Hi,

Please recommend a yeast for my barleywine. It's an extract batch.
Calls for:

6.6 lbs amber malt extract
6 lbs light dme
20 hbu galena (boil)
1 oz willamette (finish)

The recipe calls for dry champagne yeast, but I'm not sure I want to
use that. The one I used for mead ferments up to 18%. I'm thinking that
10-12% would be more appropriate.

thanks,

jon
