You've got the procedure right, the only thing I'd think twice about is
what was in your rauchbier recipe?  I'd be a little worried that some
notes of the smokiness might carry over.  It should be subtle, if it does
at all.  Maybe that's not a bad thing?

If you're worried about it, you don't need to re-pitch.  Just use a couple
fresh packets and you should be OK.

Sanitation shouldn't be a problem.  Just cover the carboy with foil or
something between bottling the rauchbier and brewing the barleywine.  There
shouldn't be any significant risk, it should maintain it's sanitation.

John.
